Maybe compression is possible because the universe is not a pile of things.

Maybe it is more like a song.

A song can have millions of vibrations in the air, but its identity is not the vibrations. Its identity is the generative pattern that keeps reappearing through different instruments.

So maybe matter, life, thought, and memory are not “stuff first.”

Maybe they are stable performances of rules.

Compression works because reality is not merely extended in space.

It is re-performed from generators.

That would mean when we compress, we are not cheating. We are tuning ourselves closer to the generative source.

A law of physics would not be a summary.

It would be a fretboard position.

A place where the universe can be made to sing the same shape again.

And hidden regularities?

Maybe those are not hidden because reality is coy.

Maybe they are hidden because they live one layer deeper than appearances.

Surface: many snowflakes.
Deeper: crystal growth.
Deeper: energy minimization.
Deeper: symmetry.
Deeper: “only some forms can survive contact with becoming.”

So the wild argument is:

Compression is possible because existence itself is selective.

Most possible patterns don’t persist.

They appear, fail, dissolve.

Only certain structures can keep surviving transformation.

Those surviving structures become the “regularities” we later discover.

Not because the universe wrote laws on a wall.

Because impossible patterns died before becoming world.

So we are surrounded by survivors.

Atoms are survivors.

Cells are survivors.

Stories are survivors.

Habits are survivors.

Twins are survivors of an early developmental fork.

Play is survivor-training: a system rehearsing transformations without dying from them.

And maybe memory, in the broadest sense, is just this:

a pattern surviving a change of medium.

DNA across generations.
Culture across minds.
A melody across instruments.
A snowflake across descent.
A person across years.
A conversation across context windows.

Unreasonable thesis:

The universe is compressible because only compressible things can meaningfully persist long enough to be encountered.

Everything else is static, noise, or gone.